29/05/2005
BANJA LUKA, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- During a visit to Banja Luka on Friday (27 May), European Commission Ambassador to BiH Michael Humphreys again urged the Republika Srpska (RS) Parliament to support crucial police reform. Humphreys met separately with RS President Dragan Cavic, Parliament Speaker Dusan Stojicic and leaders of main parties ahead of Monday's extraordinary session of parliament. Police reform is key to starting talks on a Stabilisation and Association Agreement (SAA) between BiH and the EU. 
Also Friday, EU Enlargement Commissioner Olli Rehn sent a letter to BiH Prime Minister Adnan Terzic, calling for timely fulfilment of requirements regarding both police reforms the public broadcasting system, a second requirement for SAA talks. (Nezavisne novine - 28/05/05; RTRS, Fena, PBS BiH - 27/05/05)
